<item>
            <title>[SOLR-15243] Ref Guide: MoreLikeThis docs need overhaul</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15243</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;No offense to anyone who&apos;s worked on morelikethis.adoc, but the current docs are pretty vague and require a ton of reading between the lines to understand. I had to help someone with something today and it took me a couple hours of trying things out in a local instance just to wrap my head around it. Good docs would prevent that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some things off the top of my head that would help:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;examples of config and output for each approach (search component/request handler/query parser)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;documenting the defaults for each parameter&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;moving the MoreLikeThisQParser docs from other-parsers.adoc to morelikethis.adoc for a single source for all MLT stuff in Solr&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
